snippet.textDisplay:
Ok everyone.. Stop hating on Dan. Yes, he did call Stephen "just an employee", didn't respect him as much as Hosuh (?), but does that give you the right to hate on Daniel? No. I'm not having sides here, but there's no need to harass Dan. Yeah, maybe he's selfish, but remember, he's the one who posts the videos, edits them, and gets everyone to make them. It's a big job if I was him. Anyway, he didn't have the right himself to disrespect Stephen. But that's like the same of you all hating on Dan.. Like on the end on the Cooking with Hosuh video, it shows Daniel actually works until 10/7pm to get home and make these videos for us. Some people actually really underestimate Dan. I'm not sticking up for him. But, what about Hosuh? He's probably really stressed about the situation aswell. Stephen dragged him in to the argument. Saying that, it was Daniel and Stephen's argument. So you all had no right to butt in to the argument. Do you know that you could be hurting Dan himself? There's no need for the hate. Stephen quit, Stephen quit. It might be hard to take in, just respect his desicion, ok? Yeah, Daniel may have been mean to Stephen. Daniel is underestimated ultimately though. He seems like he's been through a rough time, and been really stressed, could this be the cause of his selfishness? Like I said earlier, he said he worked majority of the day only to go home and have to edit/make videos for the rest of his night. Stephen himself said it was more of a hobby than a job, but Daniel took it seriously, and he didn't get as much money as he wanted.. I know you all hate Dan for multiple reasons, like not including him at the start of the channel, etc, but, does that give you a right to hate on him? He's only human after all.. All Dan needs is to be less selfish.. not in a mean way. I don't mean to hate on Stephen or Daniel here, I just want to say that Daniel shouldn't be hated...




Well, we need to wait for Dan's story now..
